item.title: CVE-2016-5684|2024-08-06T01:08:00.415Z -- freeimage -- freeimage
item.description: An exploitable out-of-bounds write vulnerability exists in the XMP image handling functionality of the FreeImage library. A specially crafted XMP file can cause an arbitrary memory overwrite resulting in code execution. An attacker can provide a malicious image to trigger this vulnerability.
